<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 8:41PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Thunderstorms with locally very heavy rain and strong wind gusts
will continue to develop northward and impact portions of western
Forsyth and northwestern Davidson Counties through 945 PM EDT...
At 839 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms near Bermuda
Run, or 9 miles east of Mocksville, moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and locally heavy rainfall
amounts of one to two inches in the next hour.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Huntsville, Lewisville and
Donnaha.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
